flowRoot.flowPara: Co-founder of this Startup, where I did design and setup an electronic platform to generate and manage project using Open Source tools like SugarCRM, Subversion and Redmine. The core is written in .Net. The Startup is part of the Microsoft's BizSpark program
BizSpark / Visual Studio .Net / SugarCRM / Subversion / Redmine

I worked as an External Engineer, developing software projects in different departments. Most of the projects were developed using framework .Net, writing data providers used to connect the auto service machines from Belltech with the client's data sources. I did also worked with the Interactive Voice Response department, developing tools to store and convert data generated by the systems. I also design and implement a Continuous Integration circuit using TFS, Teamcity, Redmine and Moodle
Visual Studio .Net / SOAP / APIs / AJAX / MySQL / TFS / ATM / TeamCity / Continuous Integration / Redmine / Moodle

Teacher for the class 'Technological Research Seminar', dictated every second semester in the carrer Computer Engineering in the Puerto Montt Campus. Through the class we investigate robotics, creating out own robots, using computer parts and our own electronic and mechanic, working in a Linux environment. We design an open architecture, creating apps to control our robots and drivers to interact with the hardware. In time we create new versions of this platform, designing a framework to develop project that require hardware integration, using Linux, called Monobotics, based on Mono
Linux / PCBot / Mono / Monobotics / Hardware / Robotica / Drivers

I did start working as Software Developer using Microsoft technologies and managing a Linux based network. One of the projects developed during this period was a web Rapid Application Development (RAD), wroted mainly in Javascript, using ASP.Net to access to persistence tier implemented in SQL Server 2005. Using this tool we develop multiple projects in different companies in the area. In relation with Network Administration I did setup and manage multiple services required by the office using servers running VMWare and RedHAT

In the year 2012 the company was acquired by the norwegian company Mercatus, so we migrated our services from Linux to Microsoft, maintaining the use of VMWare and ESXi. In this period we develop web projects using the .Net framework 3.5 and 4.0 with SQL Server 2005 and 2008 also Reporting Services and DotNetNuke. Also I did participate in the design and implementation of best practices and services for continuous improvement for our workflow, using Scrum and Continuous Integration
In the year 2010 I left the team, but I keep working remotely, maintaining and adding new features to the systems developed before, using Microsoft SQL Server 2005, 2008 and Reporting Services
Visual Studio .Net / Linux / Microsoft / VMWare / ESXi / Scrum / Subversion / Mono / RAD / Continuous Integration
